OL,3,CSouthport killer may have targeted
OL,4,Cchildren because of 'society value'
OL,6,FAsked about his brother's motivation
OL,7,Ffor the attack, Dion said: "Children
OL,8,Fare very valuable to society in that
OL,9,Fthey are society's future and it would
OL,10,Fhurt societies particularly badly if
OL,11,Fsomething like this happened.
OL,13,F"This is only a thought I have had in
OL,14,Fretrospect."
OL,16,FHe said he never heard his brother
OL,17,Fexpress concerning views about women
OL,18,For girls, and believed he held
OL,19,Fmainstream views but with an "unusual
OL,20,Fintensity or depth of feeling".
