OL,6,FHe said by this point he believed his
OL,7,Fbrother had gone for a walk and said:
OL,8,F"I did not believe he intended to harm
OL,9,Fanyone and thought if he was carrying
OL,10,Fa knife it was to protect himself, not
OL,11,Fto harm others."
OL,13,FAsked if he should have contacted
OL,14,Fpolice over his fears, he said: "It
OL,15,Fwas not sufficient for me to do so."
